Project: Next.js 15 blog platform with protected admin CMS, PostgreSQL, S3 uploads, and static-friendly public pages.

Module structure
- `app/`
- `app/(public)/page.tsx`, `app/(public)/about/page.tsx`, `app/(public)/posts/[slug]/page.tsx`, `app/(public)/tags/page.tsx`, `app/(public)/tags/[slug]/page.tsx`
- `app/admin/login/page.tsx`, `app/admin/layout.tsx`, `app/admin/posts/page.tsx`, `app/admin/posts/new/page.tsx`, `app/admin/posts/[id]/edit/page.tsx`
- `app/api/upload/route.ts`, `app/rss.xml/route.ts`, `app/robots.txt/route.ts`, `app/sitemap.ts`
- `app/loading.tsx`, route-level `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`
- `components/`
- `components/ui/*` from shadcn/ui
- `components/admin/post-form.tsx`, `components/admin/post-list.tsx`, `components/editor/markdown-editor.tsx`
- `components/site/header.tsx`, `components/site/footer.tsx`, `components/site/post-card.tsx`, `components/site/theme-toggle.tsx`
- `lib/`
- `lib/auth.ts`, `lib/auth-config.ts`, `lib/env.ts`, `lib/prisma.ts`, `lib/s3.ts`, `lib/revalidate.ts`
- `lib/db/posts.ts`, `lib/db/tags.ts`
- `lib/markdown.ts`, `lib/metadata.ts`, `lib/jsonld.ts`, `lib/rss.ts`, `lib/utils.ts`
- `actions/`
- `actions/posts.ts`, `actions/uploads.ts`
- `prisma/schema.prisma`, `prisma/seed.ts`
- `scripts/hash-password.ts`
- `types/post.ts`, `types/tag.ts`, `types/auth.ts`
- `middleware.ts`
- `tests/e2e/smoke.spec.ts`

Shared types and data model
- Core Prisma models: `User` optional, `Post`, `Tag`, join table `PostTag`, and optionally `Asset` only if upload metadata must be persisted later.
- `Post` fields should include `id`, `slug`, `title`, `excerpt`, `content`, `coverImageUrl`, `status`, `publishedAt`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`.
- `Tag` needs `id`, `name`, `slug`.
- Use Zod schemas for env validation and for post form/server action input to keep client/server validation aligned.
- Prefer server-side DTOs in `types/*` only where Prisma types should not leak directly into UI.

